## PART 8: SECURITY BEST PRACTICES

### DANGEROUS: shell=True with user input

```python
import subprocess

# ❌ WRONG - Shell injection vulnerability!
user_input = "example.com; rm -rf /"
result = subprocess.run(
    f'ping {user_input}',
    shell=True,
    capture_output=True,
    text=True
)
# This could delete everything!
```

---

### SAFE: List format (no shell)

```python
import subprocess

# ✅ SAFE - No shell injection possible
target = "example.com"
result = subprocess.run(
    ['ping', '-c', '4', target],
    capture_output=True,
    text=True
)

print(result.stdout)
```

---

### Input Validation

```python
import subprocess
import re

def safe_ping(target):
    # Validate IP/domain format
    if not re.match(r'^[a-zA-Z0-9.-]+$', target):
        raise ValueError("Invalid target")
    
    result = subprocess.run(
        ['ping', '-c', '4', target],
        capture_output=True,
        text=True,
        timeout=10
    )
    
    return result.stdout

print(safe_ping("google.com"))
```

